Each folder contains Kubernetes YAML manifests:

web-deployment.yaml â†’ web Deployment + Service

mobile-deployment.yaml â†’ mobile Deployment + Service

ingress.yaml â†’ ALB Ingress with ACM certificate ARN

ğŸ›  Step 2: Install ArgoCD in EKS
kubectl create namespace argocd
kubectl apply -n argocd -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/argoproj/argo-cd/stable/manifests/install.yaml


Get ArgoCD password:

kubectl get pods -n argocd
kubectl get secret argocd-initial-admin-secret -n argocd -o jsonpath="{.data.password}" | base64 -d


Port-forward to login:

kubectl port-forward svc/argocd-server -n argocd 8080:443


Open â†’ https://localhost:8080 â†’ Login with admin + password above.

ğŸ›  Step 3: Connect Git Repo to ArgoCD

In ArgoCD UI â†’ New App:

Application Name: zaltix-apps

Project: default

Sync Policy: Automatic (for GitOps)

Repository URL: GitHub repo (https://github.com/<user>/zaltix-k8s-manifests.git)

Path: / (root, or web/, mobile/, etc.)

Cluster: EKS cluster

Namespace: default (or custom)

Click Create â†’ ArgoCD starts syncing manifests.

ğŸ›  Step 4: Update Flow

You push changes to Git (e.g., new Docker image version zaltix-web:v2).

Git repo gets updated (e.g., edit web-deployment.yaml â†’ new image).

ArgoCD detects changes and applies them automatically to EKS.

ALB + ACM + Route53 routing remain intact (Ingress handles it).

ğŸ›  Step 5: Testing

Open browser:

https://login.zaltix.com â†’ Web frontend

https://api.zaltix.com â†’ Mobile backend

Both apps run behind one ALB, secured by one ACM cert, and fully GitOps managed.

âœ… Final GitOps Benefits:

No manual kubectl apply ever again.

Rollbacks â†’ just revert Git commit.

History/audit trail of changes.

Infra + apps â†’ single source of truth in Git.



ğŸ›  kustomization.yaml (at repo root)
